{"posts":[{"no":123621395,"now":"05\/01\/17(Mon)09:37:10","name":"Anonymous","sub":"Right to work: have you already fallen for the \/human rights\/ bluepill, \/pol\/?","com":"<span class=\"quote\">&gt;(23.1) Everyone has the right to work, to free choice of employment, to just and favourable conditions of work and to protection against unemployment.<\/span><br><span class=\"quote\">&gt;\u2014Universal Declaration of Human Rights, United Nations General Assembly<\/span><br><br>Friendly reminder this doesn&#039;t mean the State has to give you a job no matter what.<br><br>It simply meana that it is the duty of the State to ensure there are no legal obstacles or cartels (a.k.a. Trusts) preventing you from accessing a given profession.<br><br>It is a different story altogether whether you make a living out of it or whether you satisfy the requirements for such profession.<br><br>## EXAMPLE 1 ##<br>It is your right to be a blogger, but don&#039;t complain if you are broke. That&#039;s your problem. You don&#039;t have a right to cash.<br><br>## EXAMPLE 2 ##<br>Not everyone can be a firefighter... Because of requirements. But everyone has a right to try.<br><br>## EXAMPLE 3 ##<br>If you want to set up a business, nobody should prevent you from doing so unless you break the law. But it is still up to you the quest for funding.<br><br>## EXAMPLE 3 ##<br>The State has the duty to manage the economy in a wise manner, so that unemployment is reduced. It also has the duty to facilitate you re-entering the workforce after having been sacked. This doesn&#039;t mean the State has to pay you a wage no matter what you do.<br><br>Rights are about removing obstacles. They are not the same as gibs or privileges.<br><br>Somebody please explain this to some leftists.","filename":"C__Data_Users_DefApps_AppData_INTERNETEXPLORER_Temp_Saved Images_lunch-atop-skyscraper-new-york-construction-workers-crossbeam","ext":".jpg","w":1042,"h":765,"tn_w":250,"tn_h":183,"tim":1493645830133,"time":1493